'''Florian Gerster''' (born 7 May 1949 in [[Worms, Germany]]) is a [[Germany|German]] [[politician]] and former [[Official|government official]].

After his [[Abitur|graduation]], he served in the [[Bundeswehr|military]] and earned a [[master's degree]] in [[psychology]] at the [[University of Mannheim]]. In 1977, he was elected to the [[Landtag of Rhineland-Palatinate|Diet of Rhineland-Palatinate]] and entered the [[German Bundestag]] in 1987, representing [[Worms (electoral district)|Worms]]. From 1991 onwards, he was appointed Minister for Federal and European Affairs and thereafter [[Minister of Labor]] of  [[Rhineland Palatinate]]. From 2002 until his resignation in 2004, he served as President of the [[Federal Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs (Germany)|Federal Employment Agency of Germany]]. Today, Gerster is a senior lecturer at the [[German University of Administrative Sciences Speyer]] and works as a freelance management consultant.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hdg.de/lemo/html/biografien/GersterFlorian/index.html|title= Curriculum Vitae of Florian Gerster|accessdate=2012-04-04 |language = German|work=Foundation for the History of the Federal Republic of Germany }}</ref> He is the brother of [[ZDF]] [[heute]] news speaker [[Petra Gerster]].

